title: High-school football | Bloom-Carroll’s defense solid in win over Circleville
text:
Austin Sorg threw a 4-yard touchdown pass to  Justin Harvey with 3:50 left, and host Bloom-Carroll (4-2, 2-1) overcame five turnovers to defeat Circleville 7-0 in a Mid-State League Buckeye Division game on Thursday night.
Circleville (4-2, 1-2) advanced to Bloom-Carroll’s 6-yard line with under a minute left, but the Bulldogs defense stopped it on fourth down to preserve the victory.
